{{Transcript|event}}
{{Transcript list|Death (NPC)|Muncher|Gargoyle (2014 Halloween event)}}

==Starting off==
===Portal to Death===
* '''Player:''' I can't believe I'm doing this. Oh well, here goes nothing!
* {{qact|The player enters the portal.}}
* '''Player:''' Well, I'm still in one piece. A good start.
* {{tact|end}}

===Attempting to pass through the gateway without talking to the Grim Reaper first===
* '''Grim Reaper:''' You may be able to wander around other people's houses, but I shall not allow it.
* {{qact|The player instantly dies.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Speaking with the Grim Reaper===
* '''Player:''' Erm... Excuse me... Could I ask...
* '''Grim Reaper:''' Speak, mortal.
* '''Player:''' Well sir, lord, erm, your highness...
* '''Grim Reaper:''' I need no title.
* '''Player:''' Well of course. Sorry. I was just wondering, what is this place?
* '''Grim Reaper:''' My house. You have found yourself here because I deem it necessary.
* '''Player:''' You do?
* '''Grim Reaper:''' Long have I had a servant performing tasks as instructed. He left my service to pass on in death. Such a role is to be replaced.
* '''Player:''' I see, so you want me to be your servant?
* '''Grim Reaper:''' Eager assumptions shall bring you regret, human. A worthy soul has already been picked for the position. My house is open now as various things need attending to before the transition can take place.
* '''Player:''' So basically you want me to tidy up some things before your new servant arrives?
* '''Grim Reaper:''' Interpret as you will, mortal.
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|I'll help out, no problem.}}
** '''Player:''' I'll help out, no problem.
** '''Grim Reaper:''' Proceeding as instructed is the best way to survive here, human. I can always see you, and I can speak with you whenever I wish as this is my domain. Go to the garden for further instructions.
** '''Player:''' Always watched. To the garden. Thank you. Much appreciated!
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|That doesn't really appeal, I'm off.}}
** '''Player:''' That doesn't really appeal, I'm off.
** '''Grim Reaper:''' So be it. Let me hasten your exit. <!--presumably teleports the player out of his house-->
** {{tact|end}}

===Speaking with the Grim Reaper again===
* '''Player:''' Hello. Err. Grim. It's me again.
* '''Grim Reaper:''' Evidently.
* '''Player:''' I am so very sorry, but could you just tell me what you want me to do?
* '''Grim Reaper:''' Repetition should not be necessary here. Go to the garden for further instructions.
* '''Player:''' Excellent. Sorry. Thank you. Pardon me.
* {{tact|end}}

===Passing through the first doorway===
* '''Gargoyle:''' We're watching you, you know.
* {{tact|end}}

===Interacting with Growler===
* '''Player:''' Here boy!
* '''Growler:''' {{overhead|Grrrrrr}}
* '''Player:''' Whoaah!
* {{tselect|He looks mad. What should you do?}}
* {{topt|Stroke him}}
** '''Player:''' Ok, touching him seems to be a bad idea.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|Try to entertain him}}
** {{qact|The player performs the dance emote for Growlwer.}}
** '''Player:''' If it's possible for a skeletal dog to smile, I think he would be now. <!-- not 100% confirmed)-->
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|Blow a raspberry at him}}
** {{qact|The player blows a raspberry at him, and gets killed by Growler.}}
** '''Player:''' Maybe that wasn't so wise. <!-- not 100% confirmed)-->
** {{tact|end}}

==The Garden==
===Attempting to enter the lounge before retrieving the skull===
* '''Gargoyle:''' Oi. Weren't you told to go to the garden first?
* '''Player:''' Ooops.
* {{tact|end}}

===Passing through the garden doorway===
* '''Grim Reaper:''' You have found my garden I see.
* '''Player:''' Woah. You made me jump. How does your voice carry so far?
* '''Grim Reaper:''' It is not your concern. Whilst in my domain you shall never be far from my gaze.
* '''Player:''' O...K.... so what exactly do you want me to do in here?
* '''Grim Reaper:''' My last servant died in here. His skull still remains and you must bring it out to prevent my next servant getting the wrong impression.
* '''Player:''' And I suppose your servant was killed by some huge man-eating spider!
* '''Grim Reaper:''' That's not your business, mortal.
* '''Player:''' Sorry I asked. I'll go find the skull and bring it back out of the garden.
* {{tact|end}}

===Grabbing the skull===
* {{tbox|pic=Servant's skull detail.png|You found the servant's skull! Now to get out of the garden!}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Passing back through the garden doorway===
* {{qact|The player is zapped by the gargoyles and the skull disappears.}}
* '''Player:''' Woah, what'd I do? Oh no, the skull's gone.
* '''Grim Reaper:''' Don't concern yourself. I had instructed the gargoyles to take it from you.
* '''Player:''' You could've let me know! I almost had a heart attack.
* '''Grim Reaper:''' Please proceed to the western-most room for your next task.
* '''Player:''' You don't waste time do you. So the room that looks a bit like your lounge. I'm on my way.
* {{tact|end}}

===Speaking with the Grim Reaper after returning the skull===
* '''Player:''' Excuse me. Can I speak?
* '''Grim Reaper:''' You may.
* '''Player:''' I've finished in the garden as you saw. Where should I be going now?
* '''Grim Reaper:''' To the room to the west. Instructions await you there.
* '''Player:''' Oh ok.
* {{tact|end}}

==Searching through the lounge==
===Attempting to go upstairs before cleaning the lounge===
* '''Grim Reaper:''' You need to listen more. Head to the western-most room, mortal.
* {{tact|end}}

===Passing through the lounge doorway===
* '''Grim Reaper:''' You made it.
* '''Player:''' You sound surprised.
* '''Grim Reaper:''' You definitely wouldn't be the first or last to die in this house.
* '''Player:''' I'm so pleased. So, to the task at hand. What should I be doing in here.{{sic}}
* '''Grim Reaper:''' If you search around the room you'll find various items. Could you kindly put them back where they belong? My diary is on the table, read this for some clues. If you tell anyone what you read, you shall die.
* '''Player:''' *Gulp*. I shall have a look.
* {{tact|end}}

===Searching the table for the diary===
* {{tbox|pic=Grim reaper's diary detail.png|You find a diary on the table. This should give some clues as to where items within the room should go.}}
* '''Player:''' Hopefully by reading this I can see clues on where to put items I find.
* {{tact|Grim Reaper's diary opens}}

===Searching the cabinet===
* {{tbox|pic=Grim robe detail.png|You found the Grim Reaper's robes!}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Searching the fish tank===
* {{tselect|Where do you want to search?}}
* {{topt|Towards the left}}
** {{qact|The fish leaps out of the tank and attack's the player's face.}}
** '''Player:''' Arrghhh! My eyes!
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|Towards the left}}
** {{tbox|pic=Human bones detail.png|You found some bones! They look decidedly human.}}
** {{tact|end}}

===Searching the bookcase===
* {{tbox|pic=Scythe sharpener detail.png|You found a scythe sharpener!}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Searching the sofa===
* {{tselect|Where do you want to search?}}
* {{topt|Underneath}}
** {{qact|A hand reaches out from under the sofa.}}
** '''Player:''' That wasn't such a good idea.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|Under the cushions}}
** {{tbox|pic=Human eye detail.png|You found someone's eye!}}
** {{tact|end}}

===Searching the grim chest===
* {{tbox|pic=Will and testament detail.png|You found someone's last will and testament!}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Searching the fireplace===
* {{tbox|pic=Voice potion detail.png|You found a 'Voice of doom' potion!}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Searching the shelf===
* {{tbox|pic=Hourglass (2014 Halloween event) detail.png|You found an hourglass!}}
* {{tact|end}}

==Everything in its right place==
===Scythe sharpener===
* {{tact|You recall the entry in the diary '...put the sharpener back in the cabinet...' and place the scythe sharpener in the cabinet.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Grim robe===
* {{tact|You recall the entry in the diary '...decided to throw them in the fireplace...' and place the robes in the fireplace.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Human eye===
* {{tact|You recall the entry in the diary '...I put the eye back on the shelf...' and place the eye on the shelf.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Voice potion===
* {{tact|You recall the entry in the diary '...I found my old 'voice of doom' potion amongst some books...' and place the potion on the bookcase.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Will and testament===
* {{tact|You recall the entry in the diary '...have to sit on that for a while...' and place the will under the sofa cushions.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Human bones===
* {{tcond|If the chest is closed:}}
** {{tact|It may be an idea to open the chest first!}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If the chest is open:}}
** {{tact|You recall the entry in the diary '...decided to lock them up in a chest...' and place the bones in the chest.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|Using the bones on Growler:}}
** {{tact|The Grim Reaper might prefer to feed his own pet.}}
** {{tact|end}}

===Hourglass===
* {{tact|You recall the entry in the diary '...hourglass today so have added that to the fish tank...' and place the hourglass in the fish tank.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===After everything's returned===
* '''Grim Reaper:''' Looks like you've returned everything to their proper locations.
* '''Player:''' Woo hoo!
* '''Grim Reaper:''' You're not finished yet, mortal. Please proceed upstairs and enter the room you find there.
* '''Player:''' Upstairs it is!
* {{tact|end}}

===Speaking with the Grim Reaper after cleaning the lounge===
* '''Player:''' Hello there. I just wanted to ask where I am to go next.
* '''Grim Reaper:''' Upstairs for your last task.
* '''Player:''' Upstairs, check.
* {{tact|end}}

==Heading upstairs==
===Entering the last doorway===
* '''Grim Reaper:''' The last room.
* '''Player:''' Good job. I'm not sure my heart can take much more.
* '''Grim Reaper:''' As you can see, ahead of you is a course of a rather vicious design. I use it to keep my servants on their toes. Test it please.
* '''Player:''' Test?
* '''Grim Reaper:''' The course hasn't been used for some time. Just want to make sure it still all works.
* '''Player:''' You've got to be kidding me.
* {{tact|end}}

===Falling for a pitfall trap===
* {{qact|The player is falls through the trap down a floor.}}
* '''Grim Reaper:''' That, you will see, was a pitfall trap. You need to walk around them.
* '''Player:''' But I didn't even see the trap.
* '''Grim Reaper:''' Look closely and you should see the joins{{sic}} of the doors on the ground.
* '''Player:''' Ah, ok. Back upstairs it is then.
* {{tact|end}}

===Finishing the course===
* {{qact|The player is zapped by the gargoyles and teleported to the beginning of the course.}}
* '''Player:''' Huh? What happened there?
* '''Grim Reaper:''' Again.
* '''Player:''' What?!?
* '''Grim Reaper:''' One more time around, just to be sure all is in order.
* {{tact|end}}

===Finishing lap 2===
* {{qact|The player is zapped by the gargoyles and teleported near the staircase.}}
* '''Grim Reaper:''' That is sufficient.
* '''Player:''' Phew.
* '''Grim Reaper:''' Come and speak with me downstairs.
* '''Player:''' I'll be right there.
* {{tact|end}}

==Finishing up==
* '''Player:''' You wished to speak with me?
* '''Grim Reaper:''' Correct. You have completed my tasks as ordered, hence your time here is done.
* '''Player:''' And I'm still alive. I rock!
* '''Player:''' So... any chance of a reward for my service?
* '''Grim Reaper:''' Hmmm. Mortals and their goal-driven attitude. One thing that shall forever elude my understanding. As you wish, but trouble me no more.
* '''Player:''' Thank you!
* '''Grim Reaper:''' Death will find you one day.
* {{qact|The player experiences a "fake" death and finds themselves out the entrance portal}}
* '''Player:''' Well. That's an experience I shall never forget!
* {{tact|end}}
